85
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,064
<i>The smell was real.</i>

86
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:10,868
<i>He truly smelled like fresh lavender.</i>

87
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:14,911
<i>It was and always will be my drug of choice.</i>

88
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:20,377
<i>I even wondered if I truly loved John...</i>

89
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:24,818
<i>...because my feelings for him were never
as powerful as my feelings for Holden.</i>

90
00:07:24,978 --> 00:07:26,548
<i>And I've always felt guilty.</i>

91
00:07:26,713 --> 00:07:30,889
<i>Because I never quite bonded
like that with Scarlett when she was a baby.</i>

92
00:07:31,418 --> 00:07:33,762
<i>It was a special kind of love.</i>

93
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:36,992
<i>Maybe</i> a <i>once-in-a-lifetime thing.</i>

94
00:07:38,491 --> 00:07:39,595
<i>And then he disappeared.</i>

95
00:07:39,759 --> 00:07:40,794
<i><i>Holden!</i>

96
00:07:41,594 --> 00:07:42,902
Holden!

97
00:07:44,097 --> 00:07:45,735
Holden.

98
00:07:46,266 --> 00:07:47,404
Holden!

99
00:07:54,407 --> 00:07:58,822
<i>At first, every time you hear the phone,
you think they've found him.</i>

100
00:08:01,181 --> 00:08:03,491
<i>Your hear! pounds.</i>

101
00:08:04,584 --> 00:08:05,995
Hello'?

102
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,496
<i>Then after a month or so...</i>

103
00:08:09,789 --> 00:08:11,598
<i>...the phone is just the phone.</i>

104
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,602
<i>You do whatever you need to do
