105
00:08:16,262 --> 00:08:17,866
<i>Because you tell yourself...</i>

106
00:08:18,031 --> 00:08:20,136
<i>"lime is on your side,.</i>

107
00:08:22,602 --> 00:08:25,344
<i>And then a year has gone by
and you understand...</i>

108
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:28,877
<i>...that the next year
will not be much different.</i>

109
00:08:30,043 --> 00:08:32,785
<i>This feeling will never go away.</i>

110
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:35,153
<i>Because there is no getting over it.</i>

111
00:08:35,315 --> 00:08:38,159
<i>There is no getting to the other side.</i>

112
00:08:51,965 --> 00:08:53,342
<i>I do carry on.</i>

113
00:08:53,967 --> 00:08:56,004
<i>Mostly for Scarlett.</i>

114
00:08:56,403 --> 00:08:59,680
<i>But there are many days
when I don't really know why.</i>

115
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:02,983
<i>Same days are bearable.</i>

116
00:09:04,077 --> 00:09:06,182
<i>Today is very hard.</i>

117
00:09:06,646 --> 00:09:08,387
Alex?

118
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,357
Are you with us?

119
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:13,153
We haven't heard a lot from you, Alex.

120
00:09:16,089 --> 00:09:18,091
I don't know what to say.

121
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:24,537
I'm afraid the truth about how I'm feeling
wouldn't be very helpful.

122
00:09:24,998 --> 00:09:27,842
This is the right place
for you to speak your truth.

123
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:30,072
And the right time.

124
00:09:31,671 --> 00:09:33,912
Honestly, I'm angry.

125
00:09:36,042 --> 00:09:38,579
I mean, I don'! understand, Scarlett.

126
