It's like...

127
00:09:42,849 --> 00:09:45,090
...you're trying to hurt me.

128
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:48,357
Us.

129
00:09:49,689 --> 00:09:52,898
I don't have the sense
that Scarlett holds any ill will.

130
00:09:53,059 --> 00:09:57,735
Her stories strike me <i>as</i> being more about
wanting to alleviate your pain.

131
00:09:57,897 --> 00:09:59,808
Wanting the family whole again.

132
00:09:59,966 --> 00:10:02,970
You're both wrong.
It's not about my mother or the family.

133
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:05,241
It's what happened.

134
00:10:05,405 --> 00:10:07,078
Scarlett.

135
00:10:07,307 --> 00:10:10,618
Tell us the story
exactly how you remember it.

136
